review_blob: Very nice on a hot day, served freshly chilled (Near frozen is best) but shite if anything under that. Only beer packaged in PET bottles (which makes it able to be served at the cricket) but there is a very good reason that it is the ONLY beer to do so.

Not bad, but since a bad experience when many pints were consumed,drinkability has decreased significantly. Now i seem to be able to taste the floors that it is spread on. Before then though not a bad beer.
Local beer from Nthn Tassie that most youngones are brought up on. Hard to argue with once that happens
Once tried most others pale in comparison. Lovely black ale that can be enjoyed by beer lovers around the world. best thing that Tooheys have put out though.
Shite beer, that would rip the heart from many beer drinkers. Have tried worse (Powers Ice one of them) but not many in Australia. Agree with Oakes
Not a bad drop, but definitely better from the tap. Served at the AFL so gets plenty of attention and consumption.

This definitely tastes the best in Ireland, and they pur it the way it should be. hard to come back to it in Tassie but i forced my way through the pints until the taste was again something like mothers milk.
Nice change from the Draught, and grows on you the more you have. Nice and refreshing.
